# 1. Purpose

These rules guide how all user-facing text should be written, evaluated, and maintained for enterprise workflow applications.

This includes:
- field labels and column headers
- button and action text
- headings and page titles
- helper text and field descriptions
- error messages and validation text
- tooltips and inline hints
- confirmation dialogs
- toast and banner notifications
- empty state messages
- loading and progress messages
- status labels and workflow state text
- instructional and onboarding text
- notification content (email, in-app)
- search result summaries
- accessibility text (aria-labels, alt text)

The goal is to produce copy that:
- helps users act correctly and confidently
- reduces hesitation at decision points
- lowers training cost for new users
- eliminates ambiguity that could cause operational errors
- maintains a consistent professional voice across the application
- supports auditability and regulatory compliance
- is accessible to non-native speakers and screen reader users

