# Appendix B: Copy Evaluation Checklist (Quick Pass)

Use this for rapid first-pass evaluation. Answer Yes/No for each:

- [ ] Is every label immediately understandable to a domain expert?
- [ ] Does every button describe the specific action it performs?
- [ ] Is the same term used for the same concept across all screens?
- [ ] Are error messages specific — identifying the field, the problem, and the fix?
- [ ] Do confirmation dialogs name the action and state the consequences?
- [ ] Are status labels clear and unambiguous?
- [ ] Is the tone professional and consistent (no playfulness, no system anthropomorphism)?
- [ ] Are required fields clearly marked?
- [ ] Do fields with complex formats have helper text or examples?
- [ ] Are system internals hidden from all user-facing text?
- [ ] Do empty states explain the situation and suggest next steps?
- [ ] Are dates displayed in unambiguous formats?
- [ ] Are currency amounts formatted with symbol and unit?
- [ ] Do icon-only buttons have tooltips and aria-labels?
- [ ] Are notification texts specific and actionable?
- [ ] Are abbreviations defined on first use?
- [ ] Is destructive action text specific and distinct from safe actions?
- [ ] Are multiple validation errors shown simultaneously (not one at a time)?
- [ ] Is helper text informative (not just restating the label)?
- [ ] Would all text survive translation to another language without ambiguity?
